abstract: Czech Republic Pres Milos Zeman decides not to attend military parade, commemorating 70th anniversary of end of World War II in Moscow; event is being boycotted by other European leaders because of Russia's involvement in Ukrainian conflict.
lead_paragraph: Reversing course, President Milos Zeman of the Czech Republic said he would not attend a military parade commemorating the 70th anniversary of the end of World War II in Europe.

headline.main: Czech Leader Won’t Attend Moscow Parade After Criticism
headline.print_headline: Europe; Czech Republic: President to Skip Parade in Moscow
